# WHAT IT IS
#   Qore is "a modular, multi-threaded scripting language with
#   optional strong typing, procedural and object-oriented
#   features, built-in SQL integration, HTTP/2 and HTTP/3
#   support, and a clean syntax designed for readability".
#   Designed for vertical business-solution development with
#   embeddable program logic + arbitrary capability
#   restrictions ("a Qore application can support embedding
#   and arbitrarily restricting user-defined logic also
#   written in Qore").  Threading is built-in and Qore favors
#   multi-threaded performance over single-threaded.  This 2.3
#   release ships an IR execution engine, LLVM JIT compilation
#   with tiered execution, and AOT compilation support for
#   scripts and user modules.
#
#   Companion tooling shipped in the same workspace:
#     qcc / qdiff / qdp / qfmt / qget / qjar / qls /
#     qore-asyncapi-gen / qore-extract-qm-metadata /
#     qore-i18n / qore-onnx / qore-openapi3-gen /
#     qpatch / qschema / qdx / qdbg{,-remote,-server,-vsc-
#     adapter} / sqlutil / rest / saprest / sfrest /
#     schema-reverse  (covered separately in the corpus
#     where present)
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from man/qore.1 manpage —
#                       a comprehensive set of options for
#                       the IR / JIT / AOT execution stack;
#                       extracted via `gh api repos/
#                       qoretechnologies/qore/contents/man/
#                       qore.1`)
#
#   qore [OPTIONS] [PROGRAM-FILE] [PROGRAM-ARGS...]
#
#   When invoked without a program file and stdin is a terminal:
#     starts an interactive REPL.
#
#   General options:
#     -h, --help                     Show usage information
#                                    and exit
#     -V, --version                  Show version + build +
#                                    library info and exit
#     --short-version                Show only the version
#                                    number and exit
#     --version-animation            Show an animated 3D
#                                    version logo and exit
#     -c, --charset=<ENCODING>       Set the default character
#                                    set encoding
#     -D, --define=<KEY>[=<VALUE>]   Set a parse define
#                                    (repeatable)
#     -e, --exec=<CODE>              Execute the given code on
#                                    the command line
#     --exec-mode=<MODE>             Execution mode
#                                    (ir | jit | aot | interp)
#     --ir-dump                      Dump the IR
#     --ir-fallback-warn             Warn on IR fallback
#     --ir-fallback-report           Report IR fallbacks
#     --jit-ir-threshold=<N>         JIT IR threshold
#     --jit-jit-threshold=<N>        JIT JIT threshold
#     -l, --load=<MODULE>            Load a Qore module
#                                    (repeatable)
#     -m, --show-module-errors       Show module errors
#     -p, --set-parse-option=<OPT>   Set a parse option
#                                    (repeatable)
#     -x, --exec-class[=<CLASS>]     Execute as class (default
#                                    class derived from program)
#     -X, --eval=<EXPR>              Evaluate the expression
#                                    and print the result
#     -z, --time-zone=<ZONE>         Set the time zone
#     -b, --disable-signals          Disable signal handlers
#     -g, --disable-gc               Disable the garbage
#                                    collector
#
#   Warnings:
#     -r, --warnings-are-errors      Treat warnings as errors
#     -W, --enable-all-warnings      Enable all warnings
#     --strict-warnings              Enable strict warnings
#                                    (alias for -W)
#     -w, --enable-warning=<NAME>    Enable a specific warning
#                                    (repeatable)
#     -i, --list-warnings            List all available
#                                    warnings and exit
#     -o, --list-parse-options       List all parse options
#                                    and exit
#     -H, --parse-option-help        Show parse-option help
#                                    and exit
#
#   Compilation (LLVM JIT / AOT):
#     --compile                      Compile the script to
#                                    native code (AOT mode)
#     --output=<FILE>                Output file for --compile
#     --opt-level=<N>                LLVM optimization level
#                                    (0-3)
#     --target=<TRIPLE>              LLVM target triple
#                                    (cross-compile)
#     --show-targets                 List available LLVM
#                                    targets and exit
#     --static                       Statically link the
#                                    compiled binary
#     --compile-module               Compile as a Qore module
#                                    (.qm)
#
#   Module paths:
#     --module-dir                   Show the system module
#                                    directory and exit
#     --user-module-dir              Show the user module
#                                    directory and exit
#     --module-path                  Show the module search
#                                    path and exit
#     --module-api                   Show the current module
#                                    API version and exit
#     --module-apis                  Show all supported module
#                                    API versions and exit
#     --latest-module-api            Show the latest module API
#                                    version and exit
#
#   Licenses:
#     --lgpl                         Show LGPL license text
#                                    and exit
#     --mit                          Show MIT license text and
#                                    exit
#
#   Introspection:
#     -s, --show-charsets            Show all supported
#                                    character sets and exit
#     -a, --show-aliases             Show charset aliases and
#                                    exit
#     -B, --show-build-options       Show build-time options
#                                    and exit
#
#   REPL / interactive:
#     --interactive                  Force interactive REPL
#                                    mode (even with a script
#                                    file or non-TTY stdin)
#     --no-repl                      Disable the REPL even
#                                    when stdin is a TTY
#
#   Debug:
#     -G, --enable-debug             Enable debug support
#     -M, --modern                   Force `%modern` parse
#                                    defaults (the implicit
#                                    default for `.qr` files)
#     --no-global-vars               Disable global variables
#     -d, --debug=<LEVEL>            Set debug level
#     -t, --trace                    Enable tracing
#     --only-first-exception         Stop on first exception
#
